      "text": "Handled user input and form submission events efficiently. Implemented loading states and error handling for better UX. 3. Client-Server Communication Used the Fetch API to send and receive data between the frontend and backend. Structured and sent JSON payloads securely to the server. Processed server responses and displayed appropriate feedback to users. 4. Backend Development with Node.js and Express Designed RESTful API endpoints to handle form submissions. Parsed and validated incoming JSON data on the server. Implemented server-side logging and error handling. 5. Project Structure and Best Practices Organized code into logical components and modules for scalability. Followed best practices for file naming, code formatting, and documentation. Used version control (Git) for collaborative development and code management. 6. Problem Solving and Debugging Diagnosed and resolved bugs in both frontend and backend code. Utilized browser developer tools and server logs for effective debugging. Technologies Used",
